"title": "4474: manna",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4474: manna",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The source of food provided miraculously for the children of Israel during their desert wanderings. The NT sees this heavenly food as a symbol of Jesus Christ as the bread of life.</p>\n<h2>Manna provided by God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:31\">EXO 16:31</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh5:12\">JOS 5:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:32-Exod16:35\">EXO 16:32–16:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:6-Num11:9\">NUM 11:6–11:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:15\">NEH 9:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:24-Ps78:25\">PSA 78:24–78:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:31\">JHN 6:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:49\">JHN 6:49</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:4\">HEB 9:4</a></p>\n<h2>Manna as a type</h2>\n<h3>A type of the word of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:3\">DEU 8:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:16\">DEU 8:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:20\">NEH 9:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:4\">MAT 4:4</a></p>\n<h3>A type of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:50-John6:51\">JHN 6:50–6:51</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:32-John6:35\">JHN 6:32–6:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:47-John6:48\">JHN 6:47–6:48</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:52-John6:58\">JHN 6:52–6:58</a></p>\n<h3>A symbol of future blessing</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:17\">REV 2:17</a></p>",
